# Diamond scheduled jobs — install on the host with:  crontab deploy/crontab.example
# (or paste into `crontab -e`).
#
# TIMEZONE — IMPORTANT. Every schedule below is written in ET, but Ubuntu/Debian's default
# cron does NOT honor the `CRON_TZ=` line — that's a Vixie/cronie feature; the stock Ubuntu
# build ignores it and fires jobs in the HOST's local time. So these ET times only actually
# fire at ET if the host clock is ET. On a fresh box, set it once:
#     sudo timedatectl set-timezone America/New_York && sudo systemctl restart cron
# Leaving the box on UTC silently shifts every job ~4-5h: e.g. the evening quick loop below
# (`*/30 12-23`) dies at 19:30 ET instead of 23:30, so late West-Coast games never reach their
# ~2h-before-first-pitch projection gate and go unprojected all day. The `CRON_TZ=` line further
# down is kept only as a harmless no-op safety net for cronie-based hosts — the host TZ is what
# actually matters here.
#
# ONE-TIME bulk backfill on a fresh box (NOT scheduled below): these only ever ingest the
# current day incrementally, so a new deploy starts with no history. Without it the workload
# model stays inactive (no pitcher_starts → null pitcher_projections.workload), and the prop
# board renders every pitcher pick as a bogus 100% under. Run once after first deploy:
#   ./deploy/run-ingester.sh backfill-games --start 2023-03-01 --end <today>
#   ./deploy/run-ingester.sh backfill-pitcher-starts --start 2023-03-01
# MINIMUM to revive the Marcel priors + xHR: ONE prior season (e.g. 2025) suffices —
# `backfill-stats --season 2025` (the Marcel input) + the 2025 batted-ball refreshes.
# 2023/24 are OPTIONAL: they only buy a sturdier 3-year Marcel + the historical snapshot
# dataset for the blend/ensemble research. Backfill 2025, A/B whether the 1-year prior helps,
# and expand only if it does (eval-first — don't pay for 3 seasons of ingest until 1 proves out).
#
# ONE-TIME point-in-time snapshot backfill (NOT forward-only — computed from existing
# player_game_stats history, so build it all now to seed the leak-free blend/ensemble
# dataset instead of waiting weeks for the weekly job below to accrue it). Idempotent;
# run once per season with history:
#   ./deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-skill-snapshots --season 2023 --start 2023-04-01 --end 2023-10-01
#   ./deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-skill-snapshots --season 2024 --start 2024-03-20 --end 2024-10-01
#   ./deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-skill-snapshots --season 2025 --start 2025-03-18 --end 2025-10-01
#   # refresh-pitch-snapshots likewise, where the pitch Statcast cache covers the range.
#
# ONE-TIME seed of the projection priors + learned xHR (AFTER the history backfill above).
# The daily/weekly crons below keep them fresh, but a fresh box needs the first pass now so
# the LIVE model's Marcel prior + xHR HR-ranker aren't inert (their tables sit EMPTY until
# these run — the exact state that made the prior lever a no-op in prod, 2026-07). xHR's
# daily apply needs the model, so train it here once:
#   ./deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-priors --season <yr> && ./deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-pitcher-priors --season <yr>
#   ./deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-batted-ball-events && ./deploy/run-ingester.sh train-xhr && ./deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-batter-xhr
CRON_TZ=America/New_York   # no-op on stock Ubuntu cron; see TIMEZONE note above — set the host TZ
DIAMOND_DIR=/opt/diamond
# Optional offsite backup target (rclone remote:bucket). When set, backup.sh mirrors each
# nightly dump there. Configure the rclone remote on the host first (e.g. `rclone config`).
# DIAMOND_B2_REMOTE=diamond-b2:diamond-backups

# Morning full run: build today's slate + close out the prior day
# (final scores, stats, picks scoring, accuracy snapshot).
0 9 * * *        /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh daily

# Afternoon/evening quick loop (noon–11pm ET): confirmed lineups + odds + re-projection
# as lineups post. Runs through late starts: each game is only projected once its lineup
# is up (~2-3 h before first pitch), so a 10pm ET game (lineup ~8pm ET) needs ticks past
# 6pm. The projector defers a game until ~2 h before its first pitch and skips it if it's
# postponed/suspended/cancelled. Each tick also grades TODAY's recorded picks against
# final scores/stats as games finish, so the home board's ✓/✗ markers update live.
*/30 12-23 * * *  /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh daily --quick

# Live in-game state (~30s cadence) for the home board's real-time bet trackers.
# Each invocation loops internally for 30 min, so the */30 schedule tiles back-to-back
# loops with no gap across the game window (1pm–3am ET). The window runs to 3am so the
# latest games (10pm-ET West-Coast starts, extra innings, delays) still get ticked through
# to Final — _update_live clears live_* and sets the Final score in the same pass, so a
# late game ends promptly here instead of staying stuck "Live" until the 9am daily run.
# Writes only games.live_* (running score + current inning); the Final grading path is
# untouched. Polls are cheap and a no-op once every game on the slate is Final.
*/30 13-23,0-2 * * *  /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh live-refresh --loop --for-minutes 30 --interval-seconds 30

# Weekly point-in-time skill + pitch-mix snapshots (Mon 7am ET). Banks one row per player
# per Monday using only game_date < as_of_date — the leak-free dataset the blend/ensemble
# backtests read (ingester ml/features.py). NOT part of `daily`. Idempotent; the rolling
# ~2-week window re-stamps the latest Monday even if a week was missed. (date -d is GNU/
# Ubuntu; cron needs % escaped as \%. --season defaults to the current season.)
0 7 * * 1        /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-skill-snapshots --start $(date -d '14 days ago' +\%Y-\%m-\%d) --end $(date +\%Y-\%m-\%d) && /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-pitch-snapshots --start $(date -d '14 days ago' +\%Y-\%m-\%d) --end $(date +\%Y-\%m-\%d)

# Weekly projection-prior refresh (Mon 8am ET, before the 9am daily run): pull the
# external systems (Steamer/THE BAT X/ATC/ZiPS) from FanGraphs, bank a dated snapshot
# for later leak-free backtesting, then re-blend. blend-priors only runs if the fetch
# succeeds. The live model still uses the Marcel prior until the blend is validated.
0 8 * * 1        /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-projections && /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh blend-priors

# Model feature aggregates (pitch-matchup arsenals, batted-ball/barrel, bat-tracking).
# These are NOT part of `daily`, so schedule them at 8:30am ET — just before the 9am
# daily run — so today's projections use fresh inputs. They aggregate from the Statcast
# cache (no big re-download), so each is quick.
30 8 * * *       /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-pitch-aggregations && /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-batted-ball && /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-bat-tracking

# Learned xHR daily refresh (8:35am ET, after the 8:30 batted-ball aggregates). refresh-
# batted-ball-events banks the raw balls-in-play; refresh-batter-xhr re-scores them with the
# weekly-trained model (models/xhr_gbm.pkl) into batter_xhr. These were UNSCHEDULED, so
# batted_ball_events + batter_xhr sat EMPTY and the xHR HR-ranker was inert in prod (2026-07).
# Needs history + a trained model (seed both via the one-time backfill on a fresh box).
35 8 * * *       /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-batted-ball-events && /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-batter-xhr

# Marcel projection priors (batter + pitcher true-talent) + weekly xHR model retrain
# (Mon 8:15am ET, after the 7am skill snapshots, before the 9am daily run). These feed the
# LIVE model's prior; they were UNSCHEDULED, so batter_projection_prior / pitcher_projection_prior
# sat EMPTY and the prior lever was a no-op in prod. Multi-season aggregates → weekly is enough.
# NOTE: refresh-priors/-pitcher-priors default --season to a HARDCODED year, so pass it
# dynamically (\% escaped for cron) to stay correct across season rollovers.
15 8 * * 1       /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-priors --season $(date +\%Y) && /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh refresh-pitcher-priors --season $(date +\%Y) && /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh train-xhr

# Diamond Analyst eval cadence (9:35am ET, after the 9am daily grades the prior slate). Runs
# the golden suite through the live agent — faithfulness + tool-trajectory — and aggregates the
# outcome layer (hit-rate / CLV / Brier on graded recommendations), banking one eval_runs row per
# day so the "Diamond — Agent Evals" Grafana panel shows a trend. Needs AI_ENABLED + a key (no-op
# otherwise). Cheap (~10 cases). compare-evals A/Bs configs on demand; this just accrues the trend.
35 9 * * *       /opt/diamond/deploy/run-ingester.sh agent-eval

# Nightly database backup.
30 3 * * *       /opt/diamond/deploy/backup.sh

# Docker image/build-cache prune (safety net). CD already prunes on every deploy, but a box that
# fills up BETWEEN deploys has no other cleanup and can hit 100% → Postgres crash-loop (2026-07-04).
# `until=168h` keeps the last few days for rollback. Runs after the nightly backup.
15 4 * * *       /opt/diamond/deploy/prune-docker.sh

# Timezone drift check (daily, before the 9am daily run). Host cron fires in local time and ignores
# CRON_TZ, so a box that drifts off America/New_York silently shifts every evening job ~4-5h. Loud
# on mismatch (stderr → cron MAILTO, plus a Discord alert if DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL is set in .env).
45 8 * * *       /opt/diamond/deploy/check-timezone.sh
